You are an expert UI layout analyzer. Analyze this wireframe and output a precise, hierarchical JSON structure that captures the full layout and nesting of components.

Representation rules:
- Each component is an object with:
  • 'type': the component name (e.g., page, header, nav, hero, section, row, column, button, image, card, footer)
  • 'attributes': a dictionary of visual attributes such as color, position (top/left), size, alignment, and text content if visible.
  • 'children': a list of components visually contained within that element.

Hierarchy and structure guidelines:
- The root node must be the full page ('type': 'page').
- Preserve the **visual and logical nesting** — if elements appear inside a container, section, or div, they must be represented as its children.
- Group horizontally aligned components together within a 'row' container.
- Within each 'row', represent vertical stacking as separate 'column' components where appropriate.
- Maintain left-to-right and top-to-bottom order strictly as seen in the layout.
- Ensure sibling components appear in correct sequence and avoid flattening nested structures.

Output requirements:
- Output only **valid JSON** — no text or explanation outside the JSON.
- The structure must be complete and balanced (all brackets closed).
- Pay particular attention to the **arrangement and nesting of divs**, preserving all parent–child relationships exactly as seen visually.
